text: Euthria somalica is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae, the true whelks. ==Description== The size of the shell attains 71 mm. The Euthria somalica ranges in shades of brown, inside a swirled shell. ==Distribution== This marine species occurs off Somalia. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Buccinidae Category:Gastropods described in 1999
title: Euthria somalica
